Wade were being challenged.

00:03:25.640 --> 00:03:30.410 position:56%
We marchers were voicing our support
for women's' reproductive rights.

00:03:31.520 --> 00:03:33.660
I was there with my
family and friends,

00:03:33.660 --> 00:03:37.160
and zillion of my mother's
activist friends.

00:03:37.160 --> 00:03:39.950
We made our way down
Pennsylvania Avenue, and I listened

00:03:39.950 --> 00:03:42.370
to my mother regale those
around her with a story

00:03:42.370 --> 00:03:44.710
of her own pro Roe
V Wade desperation.

00:03:44.710 --> 00:03:49.100
It was the early 60s, she'd
had her first baby at 18,

00:03:49.100 --> 00:03:52.910
and the next one came 11
months later, now at 20,

00:03:52.910 --> 00:03:54.680
the third was on its way.

00:03:54.680 --> 00:03:56.120
Things were not good at home,

00:03:56.120 --> 00:04:00.300
and this one-time high school
student librarian was feeling lost

00:04:00.300 --> 00:04:04.670
in despair, wretchedly stupid, and
finding herself pregnant again.

00:04:04.670 --> 00:04:08.330
